---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="About Us | MoveCostMatrix" description="Learn about MoveCostMatrix — a free, privacy-first moving cost calculator that compares DIY truck, container, and professional mover estimates." canonical="/about">
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://movecostmatrix.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://movecostmatrix.com/about" }
      ]
    }
  </script>
  <Nav currentPath="/about" />

  <main>
  <section class="bg-canvas px-4 pb-28 pt-16 sm:pb-36 sm:pt-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <span class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-mute">About</span>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">About MoveCostMatrix</h1>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body content">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Our Mission</h2>
        <p>Moving is expensive, stressful, and opaque. Most people get estimates from only one type of mover because they do not have an easy way to compare options. MoveCostMatrix was built to fix that: a single page where you can see the cost of every major moving method side by side, instantly, with no email required and no upsells.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Why We Built It</h2>
        <p>The moving industry is dominated by quote-gathering sites that exist to sell your information to movers. Every time you fill out a &ldquo;free quote&rdquo; form, your phone starts ringing within minutes. We wanted something better — a calculator that treats your privacy with the same care it treats the math. No data collection, no sales calls, no hidden agenda. Just a good-faith estimate to help you plan your move and negotiate with confidence.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">How It Works</h2>
        <p>Our calculator uses the Haversine formula to calculate great-circle distance between your origin and destination, then applies a 20% road-adjustment factor for realism. For postal codes, we use the free zippopotam.us API to look up coordinates. For city names, we use a deterministic fallback algorithm. The result is fed into three pricing models based on industry data from the American Moving and Storage Association and published rate schedules:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li><strong>DIY Truck Rental</strong> — $0.80 per mile, plus base fees typical of U-Haul and similar providers</li>
          <li><strong>Moving Containers</strong> — $1.50 per mile, reflecting PODS and 1-800-PACK-RAT pricing structures</li>
          <li><strong>Professional Movers</strong> — $2.50 per mile, based on industry averages from United Van Lines, Atlas Van Lines, and Mayflower</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All calculations are in USD and can be displayed in 7 currencies. A live slider lets you adjust the distance to see how small changes affect your total.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Design Principles</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li><strong>Privacy-first by default.</strong> Everything runs client-side. No accounts, no registration, and no tracking of your calculator inputs. We use only anonymized analytics to measure traffic.</li>
          <li><strong>No email gate.</strong> You get your estimate immediately, without entering your email address.</li>
          <li><strong>Unbiased comparison.</strong> We show all three options on every calculation. We are not paid by any mover to promote their service.</li>
          <li><strong>Accessible.</strong> Dark mode, keyboard navigation, high-contrast text, and responsive design.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>MoveCostMatrix provides estimates for planning purposes only. We are not a moving broker, moving company, or financial advisor. Always obtain binding quotes from licensed moving companies before making commitments. The rates used in our calculator are based on national averages and may not reflect your specific circumstances.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  </main>

  <Footer currentPath="/about" />
</Layout>
